section.section:
An examiner may not be appointed by the commissioner if the examiner, either directly or indirectly, has a conflict of interest or is affiliated with the management of or owns a pecuniary interest in any person subject to examination. This subsection shall not be construed to automatically preclude an examiner from being:
A policyholder or claimant under an insurance policy;
A grantor of a mortgage or similar instrument on the examiner's residence to a regulated entity if done under customary terms and in the ordinary course of business;
An investment owner in shares of regulated diversified investment companies; or
A settler or beneficiary of a "blind trust" into which any otherwise impermissible holdings have been placed.
